26 SECTION 10. IC 20-26-7-48, AS ADDED BY P.L.189-2023,
27 SECTION 10, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
28 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 48. (a) The following definitions apply throughout
29 this section:
30 (1) "Current school year" refers to a year in which the governing
31 body is required to conduct a review of school building usage
32 under section 47(c) of this chapter.
33 (2) "Enrollment" has the meaning set forth in section 47(a)(3) of
34 this chapter.
35 (b) This section applies to a school corporation only if:
36 (1) the total student enrollment for in-person instruction in the
37 school corporation in the current school year is at least ten percent
38 (10%) less than the student enrollment for in-person instruction
39 in the school corporation in a school year that precedes the
40 current school year by five (5); and
41 (2) the school corporation in the current school year has more
42 than one (1) school building serving the same grade level as a
SB 239—LS 7049/DI 152

17
1 school building subject to closure under section 47 of this chapter.
2 (c) Each school corporation shall annually report to the department,
3 in the form and on the schedule specified by the department, the
4 following information:
5 (1) A listing of all buildings owned or leased by the school
6 corporation that were originally designed as a school building.
7 (2) The following information for each building listed in
8 subdivision (1):
9 (A) Designed occupancy, regardless of current use.
10 (B) Current use (and percentage of use) for classroom
11 instruction, as special use classrooms, as office space, or as
12 storage or alternatively the building's status as transitioning
13 from one (1) use or combination of uses to another.
14 (C) The following information:
15 (i) Current average full-time equivalent student enrollment
16 for in-person instruction in the school building on
17 instructional days (as determined under IC 20-30-2) in a
18 school year.
19 (ii) Percentage of instructional use.
20 (iii) Percentage of use for other purposes.
21 (D) Self-evaluation of whether the building qualifies for
22 closure under section 47 of this chapter or the school board
23 otherwise intends to close the building and the date closure
24 will occur (if applicable).
25 (d) A school corporation that fails to report the information
26 described in subsection (c) to the department when requested by
27 the department and within the schedule specified by the
28 department shall be subject to a state tuition support monthly
29 distribution reduction of twenty-five percent (25%) until the report
30 is provided to the department. A school corporation is entitled to
31 recover the state tuition support lost as a result of a reduction
32 described in this subsection.
