19 SECTION 12. IC 20-26-7.1-5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.135-2025,
20 SECTION 7, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
21 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) If:
22 (1) a covered school building is sold to a charter school or state
23 educational institution under section 4 of this chapter; and
24 (2) the charter school or state educational institution described in
25 subdivision (1) no longer intends to use the covered school
26 building for the purposes described in section 4(l) 4(n) of this
27 chapter;
28 the charter school or state educational institution shall offer to transfer
29 the covered school building back to the school corporation that initially
30 sold the covered school building to the charter school or state
31 educational institution.
32 (b) If a school corporation described in subsection (a) declines the
33 offer to transfer a covered school building back to the school
34 corporation, the charter school or state educational institution may sell
35 or transfer the covered school building to a third party. If a charter
36 school or state educational institution sells or transfers a covered
37 school building to a third party under this subsection, the charter school
38 or state educational institution must transfer an amount equal to the
39 gain in the property minus the adjusted basis (including costs of
40 improvements to the covered school building) to the school corporation
41 that initially sold the covered school building to the charter school or
42 state educational institution. Gain and adjusted basis shall be
SB 239—LS 7049/DI 152

25
1 determined in the manner prescribed by the Internal Revenue Code and
2 the applicable Internal Revenue Service regulations and guidelines.
3 (c) A charter school or state educational institution that purchases
4 a covered school building assumes total control of the covered school
5 building and must maintain the covered school building, including
6 utilities, insurance, maintenance, and repairs. Except as provided in
7 subsection (d), in the event a:
8 (1) charter school does not use the covered school building for
9 classroom instruction; or
10 (2) state educational institution does not use the covered school
11 building for an academic purpose;
12 within two (2) three (3) years after acquiring the covered school
13 building, the covered school building shall revert to the school
14 corporation, which may sell or otherwise dispose of the covered school
15 building under IC 36-1-11.
