17 IC 20-26-7-47(h).
18 (f) For purposes of determining classroom design capacity under
19 subsection (c), if a charter school reconfigures a school building after
20 the charter school leases or purchases the school building, the
21 classroom design capacity must be determined based on the
22 reconfigured school building and not the classroom design capacity of
23 the school building at the time of the lease or purchase.
24 (g) A school corporation that receives a school building back
25 from a charter school pursuant to a petition filed under subsection
26 (c) shall pay the charter school for capital improvements the
27 charter school made to the school building minus depreciation.
28 SECTION 14. IC 20-32-6.5-3, AS ADDED BY P.L.180-2025,
29 SECTION 4, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
30 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3. (a) Beginning with the 2026-2027 school year,
31 if a school determines that a student in kindergarten through grade 8 is
32 at risk of not achieving grade level proficiency in mathematics as
33 determined by an analysis of the student's data from:
34 (1) a grade level screener approved by the department; or
35 (2) a through-year statewide assessment;
36 the school must provide intervention that meets the requirements under
37 subsection (b).
38 (b) A school shall provide intervention to a student described in
39 subsection (a) that meets the following conditions:
40 (1) The intervention includes a multitiered system of support that
41 progresses from less to more intensive support based on the
42 student's individual needs.
SB 239—LS 7049/DI 152

27
1 (2) The intervention is aligned to daily Tier I instruction and
2 standard level learning progressions.
3 (3) The intervention is:
4 (A) targeted;
5 (B) differentiated; and
6 (C) supplemental to Tier I instruction.
7 (4) The intervention:
8 (A) is aligned with evidence based instructional strategies to
9 promote conceptual understanding, procedural fluency, and
10 real world problem solving; and
11 (B) allows a student opportunities to interact, show progress,
12 and demonstrate understanding through rigorous grade level
13 content.
14 (5) The intervention includes continual assessment and in depth
15 analysis of each student's data to inform the flexible movement in
16 and out of Tiers II and III.
17 (c) Not later than fifteen (15) days after a school makes a
18 determination under subsection (a) that a student is at risk, the
19 school shall provide notice to a parent of the student regarding the
20 determination. The notification may contain the following:
21 (1) Specific information about how the student is performing.
22 (2) Information about the intervention the student will receive
23 from the school.
24 (3) A list or description of any recommended resources
25 available for use at home to support the student's academic
26 growth in mathematics.
27 (c) (d) The department shall provide guidance on the multitiered
28 system that a school is required to provide under subsection (b).
SB 239—LS 7049/DI 152

